result.name: Whitewood Coffee

reviews.text: A small cafe in the mall.  Quality and quantity of food and drink was very good.  Order was made at the entrance bar table, then they were delivered to your table.  Moderate price in the district.  Tables were a bit worn out.
You can find a cup of good coffe and delicious souffle pancake in there! Can't believe can have such a high quality of food in shek mun! The price is a bit pricey for this neighborhood tho.
Nice coffee and nice food. But the place is a little bit messy, not know whether because it's just after rush morning hour or not.

Tried the flat white in the afternoon and get a diarrhea after. Be careful!
Shop is inside a local shopping mall, which is easy to access.
They offer deserts and regular western style lunch menu, however, I didn't try

The cafe has decent setup. Bright and neat. But ventilation is not very well. 
Ordered Earl Grey tea, hand drip coffee and pancakes. Food quality was mediocre. I consider them slightly overpriced. 
Worst part is having waited 35 minutes for just a cup of tea made with teabag, after we asked repeatedly for it. 
The coffee waited for 45 minutes, after lots of argument. The coffee barista has nasty attitude and didn’t even know the origin of the beans. When I asked about my coffee, I was given loads of BS...
The coffee was basically out of favor. I think the beans were exposed for way too long. 

Would be a nice decent cafe to occasionally stop by. But the horrible service is definitely unacceptable.
